The paper focuses on Federated Learning (FL), which is a subfield of Machine Learning (ML) that deals with distributed learning across multiple clients. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also addresses the heterogeneity in resource and data among different clients, which involves issues related to distributed systems and networking, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely category as well. The proposed system also involves adaptive tier selection, which can be considered a control problem, leading to the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another likely category. The paper also discusses privacy requirements, which can be related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a new system that outperforms conventional FL in various conditions, which can be related to Artificial Intelligence (AI), leading to the possibility of cs.AI as another likely category.
